The paper deals with constructing sets of permutations with certain properties, which is a problem in combinatorics and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses algorithms for computing these sets, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the paper mentions the use of these sets in error-correcting codes, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
